text.tspan: Definition of Terms
For the purposes of this research paper, the author has provided the following operational
definitions for terms that appear in this research paper:
Evaluation: The term "evaluation" is used to "compare the quality of student
performance (i.e., a 'product') based on a judgment (i.e., a score or grade)" (Kerchner,
Assessment: The term "assessment" "is based on learning goals that students and
teachers set together, rather than goals established by an external agency, institution, or
teacher" (Kerchner, 2014, p. 183). It is not judgemental and is reflective of the
student's individual progress.
Stream: As given in the
Cambridge Dictionary
(n.d.), "stream" is defined as "a group
of school students with similar ability who are approximately the same age and are
taught together." In India, students need to choose their academic streams (such as
science, humanities, commerce) in higher grades.
Tuition: As given in the
Cambridge Dictionary
(n.d.), "tuition" is defined as "the
activity of teaching, especially to small groups of students." The term is used
exclusively for extra classes engaged by students after school that teach the school
curricula.
Coaching: As given in the
Cambridge Dictionary
(n.d.), "coaching" is defined as "the
act of giving special classes in sports, a school subject, or a work-related activity,
especially to one person or a small group." Due to the enormous number of students in
